# CodeDNA v0.7

This project uses the CodeDNA annotation standard (Python-native docstring format).

## Module docstring format (required in every Python file)

```python
"""filename.py — <what it does, ≤15 words>.

exports: public_function(arg) -> return_type
used_by: consumer_file.py → consumer_function
rules:   <hard constraint agents must never violate>
"""
```

## Editing rules

1. Re-read `rules:` before writing any logic — never violate these constraints
2. Read `Rules:` in function docstrings before writing logic there
3. Check `used_by:` after changes — callers will be affected
4. Never rename `exports:` symbols without explicit instruction
5. If you discover a constraint or fix a bug, add a `Rules:` annotation for the next agent

## Generation rules

1. Write module docstring before any imports
2. For critical functions: add a `Rules:` docstring
3. Use semantic variable names: `list_dict_orders_from_db` not `data`
